# fraBering project overview

Angular Full-Stack (generator v3.8) aviation operations app for Bering Air.

## Stack

- Client: AngularJS 1.x, ui-router, ui-grid, Socket.io client, Grunt build
- Server: Express 4, Sequelize 6, PostgreSQL/SQLite, Socket.io, Firebase Admin
- Runtime: Node ^12.22.12 — do not bump Node or major deps without approval

## Conventions

- Server API modules live under `server/api/<name>/`: `index.js` (routes), `*.controller.js`, `*.model.js`
- Routes use `auth.isAuthenticated()` or `auth.hasRole('admin')` from `server/auth/auth.service.js`
- Client modules: `client/app/<feature>/` with `*.js`, `*.controller.js`, `*.html`
- Shared config (flights, pilots, equipment) is in `server/config/environment/shared.js`

## Build & test

- Dev: `grunt serve`
- Prod build: `grunt build` then `npm start` from `dist/`
- Tests: `npm test`

## Do not

- Upgrade Angular, Express, Sequelize, or Node major versions unprompted
- Replace Grunt/Bower with modern tooling unless explicitly requested
- Change CSP / Helmet settings in `server/app.js` without security review
